nei Chukovsky is a unique account of the twentieth-century Russian experience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAuthors, RussianxDiariesx20th century. 0aAuthors, Russiany20th centuryvDiaries. 0aÉcrivains russesxJournaux intimesx20e siècle. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh1 aChukovskaya, Elena, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aErlich, Victor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErlich, Victor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeim, Michael.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013797240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300137972423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300137972/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles